data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` construction **won't compile**. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The entire expression-tree plumbing is eliminated — conditionals go directly in the lambda body.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF will auto-append a number (e.g., `Street1`). Pin names explicitly:

```csharp
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve the old name:

```csharp
b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    p.ComplexProperty(pa => pa.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
```

Either way, **a new migration will be generated** to rename columns. Review it carefully before applying to production.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (like `CommandReaderExecuting`) now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← add this
    {
        // logCommandText = redacted SQL safe for logging
        // command.CommandText = actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods in the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
